    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-11T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2470: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-11T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 11, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 11—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. In accordance with the instructions of his Government, Italian Minister
                    yesterday made a verbal protest<note n="32" xml:id="d462fn32">In despatch No.
                        424, of November 19, the Chargé corrected this statement and reported that
                        the Italian protest was communicated by written note (765.84/3028).</note>
                    against the decision of the Egyptian Government in principle to apply sanctions
                    against Italy. Italian Minister is reported to have stated by an official
                    announcement of the Government of Egypt that the Italian Government reserved the
                    right to take any action which might be deemed necessary against Egypt in the
                    event of the violation of the latter’s international engagements with Italy.</p>
                <p>Repeated to American Embassy at Rome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
